  "texts": [
    "Intuitively, the element (i, j) of the Jacobian of Eq.",
    "(4) evaluates how much the spike time of a neuron i in layer n changes if the spike time of neuron j in layer n -1 shifts by a small amount.",
    "Similarly to a ReLU network, the mask reflects the fact that in our SNN spike times only shift for active neurons where the active neurons in an arbitrary layer n 0 of our SNN are those that fire before t ðn 0 Þ max.",
    "Importantly, the causality of interactions in the feed-forward path is limited to chains of active neurons; and the backpropagation of errors via the chain rule in Eq.",
    "(3) limits the information flow backward to the same paths of active neurons, as made explicit by the mask."
